16:21.021 --> 16:23.899
-[Samantha] You wanted to be a dad?
-I don't know any Katiane.

16:23.983 --> 16:27.027
Food, homework, drive them to school.
I have a show to produce.

16:27.111 --> 16:29.530
-Here.
-Calm down. I'm the father, not the nanny.

16:29.905 --> 16:31.490
I will give you this chance, OK?

16:31.573 --> 16:33.283
Try not to ruin everything again.

16:53.262 --> 16:55.723
[blender whirs]

17:01.603 --> 17:02.980
[blender whirs erratically]

17:13.824 --> 17:16.076
I think I'll just drink
my macchiato espresso.

17:16.160 --> 17:17.911
Look, what a bilingual kid!

17:17.994 --> 17:20.497
-You know I almost played in Italy?
-I don't like soccer.

17:21.205 --> 17:24.877
Basketball?
Something more Olympic, like gymnastics?

17:24.960 --> 17:28.130
I'm more of an intellectual type.
I'm writing my autobiography.

17:28.422 --> 17:29.631
[Dodoi] Right.

17:30.340 --> 17:31.383
Brandon...

17:31.467 --> 17:34.678
it must be hard for you
to live here alone with two women.

17:34.762 --> 17:35.846
I get along with women.

17:35.929 --> 17:37.473
Just like your daddy!

17:37.556 --> 17:39.600
But now you have a buddy here, right?

17:39.683 --> 17:42.186
Everything you can't tell your mom,
you can tell me.

17:42.269 --> 17:43.604
I tell Mom everything.

17:43.687 --> 17:47.107
Yes, but I'm here
to answer any question, got it?

17:47.191 --> 17:48.233
Any questions at all.

17:48.317 --> 17:49.902
Hmm... Anything at all?

17:49.985 --> 17:52.863
Yes, any question... anything.

17:54.740 --> 17:59.036
On <i>Frozen</i>, Elsa was locked in the castle
because she had freezing powers.

17:59.369 --> 18:01.455
What was your power when you got arrested?

18:01.538 --> 18:02.748
[Cindy] Is everything OK?

18:02.831 --> 18:06.293
Everything's great!
I've made you a great breakfast.

18:06.376 --> 18:07.461
That's sweet. Thanks!

18:07.544 --> 18:09.588
But we have to hurry,
I have to go to school.

18:13.759 --> 18:17.346
-Just so you know, I'm vegan.
-Didn't your mom raise you as a Catholic?

18:17.429 --> 18:20.015
No, vegans don't eat anything
from animals.

18:20.099 --> 18:21.683
But all food comes from animals.

18:22.059 --> 18:25.896
That's delicious!
What did you put in here? Lemongrass?

18:29.775 --> 18:31.985
Guys, you know what I was thinking?

18:32.069 --> 18:34.446
I don't know, maybe we could do
something more...

18:34.530 --> 18:35.656
fun.

18:35.739 --> 18:37.116
It's my first day out.

18:37.199 --> 18:38.867
"Fun" like skipping school?

18:38.951 --> 18:40.285
Mom will kill us.

18:40.369 --> 18:43.789
Brandon, easy there, I'm your dad.
I also know what's best for my kids.

18:49.419 --> 18:50.879
I'll be damned.

18:52.714 --> 18:57.052
[stuttering] Kids, relax,
we'll do everything responsibly, OK?

18:57.553 --> 18:58.846
[kids whimper]

18:58.929 --> 19:00.931
How long since you last drove?

19:01.014 --> 19:03.392
-Twelve years, can you believe it?
-Yes!

19:03.475 --> 19:05.060
Look ahead, for the love of God!

19:05.519 --> 19:07.020
[car whizzes by]

19:07.104 --> 19:09.398
Come on, you overreacted.

19:09.481 --> 19:11.233
I'm great behind the wheel, right?

19:11.316 --> 19:13.235
-I'm good at men's stuff.
-Men's stuff?

19:13.318 --> 19:15.654
Now you'll hear about
how the world has changed.

19:15.737 --> 19:17.406
-Dad, the world's changed.
-See?

19:17.489 --> 19:19.741
And there's a kind of man
that is endangered.

19:19.825 --> 19:21.285
-Like rhinos.
-[Cindy] Exactly.

19:21.368 --> 19:24.496
Did you know there are only
2,000 rhinos left in the world?

19:24.580 --> 19:26.206
You don't want to be a rhino, Dad?

19:26.290 --> 19:27.207
No...

19:27.291 --> 19:29.877
So learn this: There's no "men's stuff".

19:30.711 --> 19:34.715
[camera shutters click]

19:35.966 --> 19:38.635
[Samantha] <i>No, I don't regret</i>
<i>anything in my life.</i>

19:38.719 --> 19:41.847
It was just another moment, you know?

19:42.431 --> 19:46.268
I'd only pose naked today
if it were for a noble cause.

19:46.351 --> 19:50.522
And it has nothing to do with my age,
because I'm still quite young.

19:50.606 --> 19:53.066
I've even promised on my Instagram page

19:53.150 --> 19:56.069
that if corruption in Brazil ends,
I'll walk naked in the street!

19:56.153 --> 19:59.239
What about Dodoi,
are you two dating again?

20:00.032 --> 20:03.744
Life is a springboard, right? [laughing]
Who can tell about the future?

20:03.827 --> 20:05.204
[Marcinho] <i>Beer commercial?</i>

20:05.287 --> 20:06.997
Of course they'll fucking do it.

20:07.080 --> 20:09.458
Beer, sausages, meds...

20:09.541 --> 20:12.211
Cigarettes...
What matters is they speak to the youth.

20:12.294 --> 20:17.007
But would you, as an adult, be willing
to give in more than when you were child?

20:17.257 --> 20:20.594
Today, just like when I was a child,

20:20.886 --> 20:24.723
I'm ready to give in to everything,
except for my career and personal life.

20:25.807 --> 20:28.018
[Ciggy] Samantha! [grunting]

20:28.101 --> 20:29.228
[Ciggy] Little Princess!

20:29.311 --> 20:32.189
-[Ciggy] Samantha!
-That's enough with this old man, right?

20:32.731 --> 20:34.691
-Little princess.
-[Samantha] Yes?

20:35.234 --> 20:39.279
-I think I'd prefer the old costume.
-Me too.

20:39.363 --> 20:42.783
But they said it's not cool anymore.
I didn't want to argue.

20:42.866 --> 20:43.784
Was this necessary?

20:43.867 --> 20:45.327
SMOKING CAUSES SEXUAL IMPOTENCE

20:45.410 --> 20:46.245
See?

21:04.805 --> 21:07.766
What?
Did I bring you here just to look around?

21:08.225 --> 21:09.643
I'll play striker!

21:10.185 --> 21:12.187
Man, I hate soccer!

21:20.696 --> 21:21.863
[man] Where's the <i>plié</i> ?

21:25.158 --> 21:26.702
[man] You're looking beautiful!

21:28.996 --> 21:30.580
Wait! Stop.

21:30.664 --> 21:31.790
[man] That's great.

21:31.873 --> 21:33.333
[Ciggy] We can stop. That's it.

21:33.417 --> 21:35.335
-See you tomorrow. Thanks!
-[dancer] Bye.

21:35.711 --> 21:36.878
Samantha!

21:37.337 --> 21:38.922
Feel free to go home early.

21:39.006 --> 21:42.217
The problem is not me, it's them.
They bounce for anything.

21:42.301 --> 21:45.762
-I want nothing to do with this!
-Go rest. You've got enough rhythm.

21:45.846 --> 21:48.598
No need to learn new choreographies.
Are you listening?

21:48.682 --> 21:50.517
Are they laughing at me? Really?

21:50.600 --> 21:54.396
Are you laughing at me?
You are nothing more than extras!

21:54.479 --> 21:56.773
Look, I don't need
these resentful jerks, OK?

21:56.857 --> 21:59.609
If I want it, I just snap my fingers
and they are fired!

21:59.693 --> 22:00.986
You got that? Wanna see it?

22:01.069 --> 22:03.071
No! We need them, dear!

22:03.155 --> 22:04.323
I need no one but myself.

22:06.199 --> 22:07.784
[Cindy] Mmm...

22:09.953 --> 22:12.039
-I defended the goal!
-With your face.

22:12.998 --> 22:14.291
Here, I deserve it more!

22:14.374 --> 22:16.501
I'm the one who got a black eye.

22:16.585 --> 22:19.463
Don't tell your mom,
that's our deal, right, son?

22:19.546 --> 22:22.716
Relax, I'll put some makeup on
and she won't even notice.

22:23.091 --> 22:24.509
Ouch, my head...

22:25.385 --> 22:26.678
Does this have pistachio?

22:26.762 --> 22:29.347
Yes! Pistachios, strawberry,
cherry, everything.

22:29.556 --> 22:32.267
-Brandon is allergic to pistachios!
-You're kidding!

22:32.350 --> 22:35.854
-I don't want to die in this dirty car!
-We have to go to the hospital now!

22:36.313 --> 22:38.690
[Dodoi] Help him, Cindy!
Stop eating the ice cream!

22:38.774 --> 22:39.983
[Dodoi] Help the boy!

22:45.405 --> 22:47.324
Will you go back to prison?

22:48.408 --> 22:50.535
No, son, I won't.

22:59.669 --> 23:03.423
LIFE - MY LONG STORY
OF ALMOST NINE YEARS

23:14.559 --> 23:15.685
You look tired.

23:15.769 --> 23:18.355
Me? No! I'm fine. Cindy didn't try to auction Brandon
on the internet?

23:21.108 --> 23:21.983
No, it's all good.

23:22.067 --> 23:24.486
Brandon didn't try to sell
his life story to Globo?

23:24.569 --> 23:27.781
None of that. After school,
we watched soap operas and they slept.

23:27.864 --> 23:30.575
Dodoi, Cindy and Brandon
quietly watching TV?

23:30.659 --> 23:31.827
[Dodoi] Mm-hmm.

23:31.910 --> 23:32.953
[Samantha laughs]

23:33.036 --> 23:36.623
Admit it, Dodoi. No need to be ashamed.
Kids are a lot of work.

23:36.706 --> 23:39.209
Ashamed of what? Of being a kickass dad?

23:39.292 --> 23:43.171
It's probably hard for those "rhinos"
who can't share tasks with women, right?

23:43.255 --> 23:45.799
And there was time for a speech by Cindy?

23:46.216 --> 23:48.093
I've been this way since I was born.

23:49.094 --> 23:50.220
Sweet...

23:52.305 --> 23:53.682
And sexy.

23:57.144 --> 23:59.938
Do you think this is a conjugal visit?

24:00.021 --> 24:02.732
Look, I spent 11 years
taking care of my kids on my own.

24:02.816 --> 24:06.153
I'm not going to congratulate you
for taking them to school.

24:10.073 --> 24:11.867
-[sighs]
-[door slams]

24:21.042 --> 24:21.960
[sighs]

24:30.552 --> 24:31.845
[gasps]

24:31.928 --> 24:33.597
[groans]

24:33.680 --> 24:35.265
[grunts]

24:36.057 --> 24:37.893
[Dodoi] So you have keys, Cig?

24:40.729 --> 24:41.938
Who's there?

24:42.522 --> 24:43.481
Is it a spirit?

24:43.815 --> 24:45.108
[Dodoi] A spirit, Cig?

24:46.067 --> 24:47.986
Fofão? [laughing]

24:48.069 --> 24:49.279
Is it you?

24:49.571 --> 24:51.072
Are you trying to make contact?

24:51.156 --> 24:53.533
-Hold on, I'll write it down.
-[Dodoi] It's Dodoi.

24:53.617 --> 24:55.452
Oh! You scared me!

24:55.535 --> 24:56.995
[laughing]

24:57.078 --> 24:59.873
I thought it was a friend.

24:59.956 --> 25:01.291
[laughing]

25:03.001 --> 25:04.920
You've been with her a long time, right?

25:05.462 --> 25:09.174
I've been her friend since the time
it was cool to be a cigarette.

25:09.257 --> 25:10.217
[laughing]

25:10.675 --> 25:12.177
[Ciggy] It's been a while...

25:14.262 --> 25:16.389
Is she giving you much trouble?

25:17.599 --> 25:19.601
I was away too long, Cig.

25:19.684 --> 25:21.603
It's hard to understand what she wants.

25:21.686 --> 25:23.730
I'm here now.
I'll help to leave this life.

25:24.314 --> 25:25.690
Leave this life?

25:26.149 --> 25:28.360
You still don't understand.

25:28.902 --> 25:30.445
[Ciggy laughs]

25:30.528 --> 25:32.822
[coughing]

25:32.906 --> 25:34.324
[Dodoi] Are you OK, man?

25:34.407 --> 25:38.119
[coughing] I'm just tired. And old.

25:38.620 --> 25:40.622
You've done it all, haven't you?

25:40.705 --> 25:43.625
[Ciggy] No!
I've got a lot of things left to do.

25:43.708 --> 25:47.587
I still have to rob a bank with a toy gun,

25:47.671 --> 25:50.674
because... who hasn't done it
with a real gun?

25:50.924 --> 25:53.385
Parachuting without an instructor...

25:53.927 --> 25:55.887
I have to make love to a man...

25:56.763 --> 25:57.847
What's the matter?

25:58.181 --> 26:01.810
Don't trust what people say,
sex with men is not so cool, Cig.

26:01.893 --> 26:03.311
[Ciggy laughs]

26:03.395 --> 26:05.855
A dancer was hitting on me today.

26:06.273 --> 26:07.607
You know what he told me?

26:08.316 --> 26:10.110
He told me he was "fluid".

26:10.193 --> 26:11.903
[chuckles] That's it, Cig.

26:11.987 --> 26:15.573
If I learned anything in prison, it's that
we have to do what makes us happy.

26:15.782 --> 26:16.950
[Dodoi] Go for it.

26:18.952 --> 26:20.328
[Samantha] <i>So many signatures!</i>

26:21.121 --> 26:23.164
Too many, Joelma!

26:23.248 --> 26:26.126
It was a little more expensive
than I had in mind,

26:26.209 --> 26:27.627
but it's good news.

26:28.837 --> 26:31.256
-[Samantha] Let me see!
-Ready? I'll show it to you!

26:33.049 --> 26:34.175
Ta-daa!

26:34.259 --> 26:36.303
"Big handbags are coming back
into fashion"?

26:37.220 --> 26:38.638
Here, on the footnote.

26:38.722 --> 26:40.890
The human eye goes
straight to the footnote.

26:40.974 --> 26:43.268
-[Samantha] What's this?
-[Marcinho] Your interview! This tiny thing? It's not even a page!

26:45.729 --> 26:48.356
I spent hours telling my intimate stuff
to that woman.

26:48.773 --> 26:52.819
And look at this! My name is misspelled.
I told her my name's not Samantha anymore.

26:52.902 --> 26:54.279
-Not Samantha anymore?
-No.

26:54.362 --> 26:56.906
It's Samantha!
With an exclamation point at the end.

26:56.990 --> 26:58.158
-Repeat it.
-Samantha.

26:58.241 --> 26:59.451
No, Samantha!

26:59.534 --> 27:01.369
"Samanthá", emphasis on the last "A".

27:01.453 --> 27:03.079
-Samanthá.
-Listen, you'll see.

27:03.163 --> 27:04.622
-Samantha!
-Samantha.

27:04.706 --> 27:06.374
-Samantha!
-Like an exclamation.

27:06.458 --> 27:08.084
-Samantha!
-Samantha!

27:08.168 --> 27:09.002
Samantha!

27:09.085 --> 27:10.545
-Samantha.
-Samantha!

27:10.628 --> 27:11.463
Samantha.

27:11.546 --> 27:13.798
"Samantha!
There's a huge line for your show."

27:13.882 --> 27:15.550
"Samantha! Your car's outside."

27:15.633 --> 27:18.053
"Samantha! Ivete went home crying."
Try it!

27:18.386 --> 27:21.973
-Ivete never goes home crying.
-You wouldn't know!

27:34.027 --> 27:35.612
[Samantha] <i>Dodoi! I'll kill you!</i>

27:35.987 --> 27:38.448
[Samantha] That's what happens
when you help someone.

27:38.531 --> 27:41.910
What happens is that you get stabbed
in the back in your own house.

27:41.993 --> 27:43.703
I want to know what this is!

27:43.787 --> 27:45.872
"Big handbags back in fashion"?

27:46.623 --> 27:49.793
