What is this?

27:49.876 --> 27:51.878
EX-SOCCER PLAYER DODOI INVADED PITCH

27:51.961 --> 27:53.254
An article about you?

27:53.338 --> 27:58.134
My interview is only this tiny piece
which you need a telescope to read.

27:58.218 --> 28:00.011
This whole page. What is this, Dodoi?

28:00.595 --> 28:02.013
I can't even see it.

28:02.097 --> 28:04.766
-You can't? Brandon?
-I don't have my glasses.

28:04.849 --> 28:06.726
Cindy, the picture is pretty big.

28:06.810 --> 28:08.228
Is it a soccer pitch?

28:08.311 --> 28:10.855
Suddenly everyone's nearsighted here.

28:10.939 --> 28:12.649
It's OK, I'll read it to you.

28:12.732 --> 28:17.570
[Samantha] "Former soccer star Dodoi
invaded Pacaembu Stadium,

28:17.654 --> 28:20.615
played soccer with his kids,
did some ball-bouncing,

28:20.698 --> 28:22.617
and took photos with fans."

28:22.700 --> 28:24.994
Can I die now? With so much cuteness?

28:25.078 --> 28:27.872
Is that why my photo came out so small
in the footnote?

28:27.956 --> 28:30.041
Samantha, I didn't see any photographers.

28:30.125 --> 28:33.545
You were supposed to take the kids
to school. Look how my son is!

28:33.628 --> 28:35.130
But I'm great!

28:35.213 --> 28:37.382
So that's what you came back for?

28:37.674 --> 28:39.300
To mess up my life?

28:39.384 --> 28:42.011
Because if so,
you should have stayed in prison.

28:57.277 --> 29:01.197
[Samantha] Put me down gently, OK?
Careful with your Cindy...

29:02.073 --> 29:06.369
<i>It doesn't matter that this place isn't</i>
<i>normal. Our lives aren't normal anyway.</i>

29:06.703 --> 29:09.581
[chuckling] She's going to be so pretty.

29:10.039 --> 29:11.875
Just like her mom...

29:16.755 --> 29:17.672
What's this?

29:18.006 --> 29:20.633
The key to our home
for when you leave here.

29:44.157 --> 29:45.492
[door opens]

29:50.038 --> 29:54.000
This is a really important night for me,
and I need my family with me.

30:05.053 --> 30:06.679
I didn't mean to say that, OK?

30:06.971 --> 30:09.766
Of course it wouldn't be better
if you'd stayed in prison.

30:10.850 --> 30:13.937
Hey... I didn't even
have to fire the old guy!

30:14.020 --> 30:16.564
It couldn't be better than this
if we tried.

30:16.648 --> 30:18.483
What are you talking about?

30:19.317 --> 30:22.278
[Ciggy] No, I was waiting
for you to ask me out.

30:22.362 --> 30:23.822
I wanted to know if you have...

30:24.823 --> 30:27.784
-[Ciggy] Stop it!
-[Samantha] That's all I needed now!

30:28.159 --> 30:30.245
Leave me, Samantha! I'm old.

30:30.328 --> 30:32.831
Stop this nonsense!
It's always been like this.

30:33.164 --> 30:35.375
Who's going to help me
if I forget the lyrics?

30:35.458 --> 30:36.584
Look at me.

30:38.044 --> 30:40.338
Get on this stage and help me shine.

30:40.421 --> 30:43.633
Marcinho is right.
Who is going to need a stinky old man?

30:43.716 --> 30:45.510
Cig! This is just the beginning.

30:45.593 --> 30:49.222
We'll make a comeback,
you and me together, on television.

30:49.305 --> 30:52.725
Samantha... television is dead!

30:52.809 --> 30:53.768
[cheering]

30:54.060 --> 30:59.357
[crowd, chanting] <i>Samantha! Samantha!</i>

31:01.860 --> 31:05.738
[crowd, chanting] <i>Samantha! Samantha!</i>

31:09.492 --> 31:11.661
[Ciggy] Dodoi, come here!

31:13.997 --> 31:15.039
It happened!

31:16.040 --> 31:17.083
Did you rob a bank?

31:17.166 --> 31:19.127
His name is Wilson, silly!

31:19.586 --> 31:22.255
-The dancer?
-Yeah, him and two others!

31:22.338 --> 31:24.883
But what they did, man,
first they grabbed me...

31:24.966 --> 31:27.719
All right, Cig. I'm glad for you!

31:27.802 --> 31:28.803
[Ciggy laughs]

31:28.887 --> 31:30.763
-I'll see how the kids are.
-OK.

31:32.056 --> 31:33.349
[sighs]

31:39.314 --> 31:43.443
[Ciggy] You are Brazil's
most beloved girl!

31:43.526 --> 31:45.403
[Ciggy] Don't forget your tiara!

31:46.279 --> 31:51.367
[crowd cheers]

31:55.371 --> 32:00.501
[pop music plays]

32:03.338 --> 32:05.840
What matters is to never stop belie...

32:06.466 --> 32:07.634
[Samantha] Cig?

32:08.927 --> 32:10.136
What's wrong, Cig?

32:10.553 --> 32:11.596
[Dodoi] Someone help!

32:11.679 --> 32:14.265
-[Samantha] Talk to me!
-[Marcinho] Come on, Samantha!

32:14.599 --> 32:15.642
Dodoi...

32:16.100 --> 32:17.644
[Marcinho] Now, for fuck's sake!

32:19.771 --> 32:21.773
Leave this old man behind, Samantha!

32:21.856 --> 32:24.192
[crowd, chanting] <i>Samantha! Samantha!</i>

32:24.275 --> 32:27.362
Do you know how much this costs?
I'll destroy your career!

32:29.572 --> 32:32.241
-Go! Call a doctor!
-[Dodoi] I need a phone.

32:32.325 --> 32:36.746
[Samantha] Call the doctor.
Cig? Talk to me, Cig.

32:43.002 --> 32:47.340
"If there is anyone reading this,
it is because I am dead.

32:49.300 --> 32:52.720
I don't have anything to say at my wake,

32:52.804 --> 32:56.140
so I decided to make a list

32:56.224 --> 33:00.687
to out every gay stud
on Brazilian television

33:00.770 --> 33:02.772
at the TV Tupi network."

33:05.775 --> 33:06.776
[woman] Stop...

33:09.570 --> 33:10.947
[woman] Thank you.

33:11.364 --> 33:14.534
If a friend would like to say something,
please...

33:18.705 --> 33:21.082
-[Dodoi] Go on.
-[Cindy] Go. Go!

33:21.165 --> 33:23.042
-[Brandon] Come on, Mom.
-[Dodoi] Go on.

33:35.930 --> 33:37.515
[Samantha's memory] <i>Samonster!</i>

33:40.101 --> 33:42.645
The happiest day of my life was...

33:42.729 --> 33:44.647
[Samantha's memory] <i>Samonster!</i>

33:48.317 --> 33:50.820
Sometimes, what we want the most...

33:52.447 --> 33:53.948
[Samantha's memory] <i>Samonster!</i>

33:56.409 --> 33:57.827
[Ciggy] Samantha!

33:57.910 --> 34:01.456
[Ciggy] What matters
is to never stop believing.

34:04.542 --> 34:09.547
[quietly] ♪ <i>When it seems like</i>
<i>The sky is getting sad </i>♪

34:10.465 --> 34:15.136
♪ <i>And the world is getting dark </i>♪

34:16.094 --> 34:21.100
♪ <i>Listen to the wind, telling you </i>♪

34:21.684 --> 34:25.271
[louder] ♪ <i>That the sun is smiling </i>♪

34:25.353 --> 34:27.607
♪ <i>Stunning </i>♪

34:27.690 --> 34:31.694
♪ <i>I'll never allow </i>♪

34:32.487 --> 34:36.824
♪ <i>Sadness to win over me </i>♪

34:37.533 --> 34:40.828
♪ <i>The world is movement </i>♪

34:40.911 --> 34:45.373
♪ <i>And now is the moment </i>♪

34:46.918 --> 34:48.710
♪ <i>Morning star </i>♪

34:49.670 --> 34:51.714
Wait, guys, didn't I park here?

34:51.797 --> 34:55.342
The car was towed, Samantha.
We better take a cab.

34:55.426 --> 34:57.053
"We" are too many people,

34:57.136 --> 34:59.097
and my house is not a hotel, OK?

34:59.806 --> 35:01.933
[car horn beeps]

35:02.767 --> 35:05.353
[tires screech]

35:08.272 --> 35:13.027
Are you that gorgeous couple
from that beer commercial?

35:13.111 --> 35:16.239
-Bullshit!
-Have I ever lied to you? Don't answer!

35:16.614 --> 35:22.870
You two were chosen to be the new faces
of a Canoe Beer commercial.

35:22.954 --> 35:24.205
Good brand, OK?

35:24.288 --> 35:26.624
When you get used to it,
it's an excellent beer.

35:26.707 --> 35:31.087
What did I tell you?
Couples sell, damn it!

35:31.337 --> 35:33.214
You know what I like about you, Joelma?

35:33.297 --> 35:35.216
You don't hold grudges.

35:35.299 --> 35:38.219
I had two options: hate you forever

35:38.302 --> 35:40.304
or make 20 percent of everything.

35:40.388 --> 35:41.931
I chose both.

35:42.265 --> 35:44.934
Huh? Let's go for a ride, kids!

35:45.434 --> 35:47.645
You know that the house is yours, right?

35:47.728 --> 35:52.275
Imagine if I'd actually listened to you
and moved out? Imagine how you'd be?

35:52.358 --> 35:55.736
You should thank me, darling.
I'm bringing you back from exile.

35:55.820 --> 35:58.906
I'm calling it "jail ostracism"
to make it more elegant.

36:01.325 --> 36:02.618
You're glad that I'm back.

36:03.953 --> 36:05.454
Don't get used to it, OK?

